The global pulse ingredients market is witnessing robust growth driven by the increasing consumer preference for plantThe global pulse ingredients market is experiencing significant growth due to the growing consumer shift towards plant-based proteins and the rising demand for clean label and sustainable food products. Pulse ingredients, such as pulse flours, starch, and proteins, offer a rich source of nutrients, including protein, fiber, vitamins, and minerals, making them attractive to health-conscious consumers. The versatility of pulse ingredients in various food and beverage applications, such as bakery products, snacks, and beverages, is contributing to their expanding use in the industry.

In terms of type segmentation, pulse flours are witnessing increasing adoption in food products due to their gluten-free properties and nutritional benefits. Pulse starch is gaining popularity as a thickening agent and for its functional properties in various food applications. Pulse proteins are experiencing high demand in sports nutrition and the plant-based products market, driven by the shift towards vegan and vegetarian diets. The versatility and sustainability of pulse ingredients make them a popular choice among manufacturers looking to cater to the growing demand for plant-based alternatives.

The application segment of the pulse ingredients market includes food & beverages, animal feed, and other industrial applications. In the food & beverages sector, pulse ingredients are being utilized in a wide range of products, including bakery items, snacks, cereals, and beverages. The increasing consumer preference for healthy and natural ingredients is propelling the growth of pulse ingredients in this segment. Furthermore, the animal feed sector is incorporating pulse ingredients as a source of protein and energy for livestock, contributing to the market expansion.

Segmentation by source showcases the variety of pulse ingredients available, including lentils, peas, chickpeas, and other pulses. Lentils are widely used in the manufacturing of pulse ingredients due to their high protein content and versatility in different applications. Peas are gaining traction in the market for their functional properties and sustainability, making them an attractive source for manufacturers. Chickpeas are also a prominent source of pulse ingredients, providing health benefits and unique flavor profiles that appeal to consumers.

